Reasoning: The paper presents a new approach to credal nets, which are graphical models that generalise Bayesian nets to imprecise probability. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
